00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:01,416
[MAN] I thought being
a magician meant having

253
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:04,208
the power to do
anything you wanted.

254
00:15:04,291 --> 00:15:07,833
That's why I took the oath
and became what I am today.

255
00:15:07,916 --> 00:15:11,000
So nothing could ever
stand in my way again.

256
00:15:11,083 --> 00:15:15,791
That's the reason. I did this
for myself and no one else.

257
00:15:18,166 --> 00:15:20,125
[MAN] It has
nothing to do with her.

258
00:15:20,208 --> 00:15:22,916
That woman dying
from a cruel curse.

259
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:26,500
A powerless, pitiful woman who
doesn't fight but smiles softly

260
00:15:26,583 --> 00:15:30,583
and accepts death as it closes
its fist around her heart.

261
00:15:31,875 --> 00:15:33,416
[groaning]

262
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:35,458
[MAN] If I couldn't help
her, then clearly that meant

263
00:15:35,541 --> 00:15:37,416
I did not possess
the boundless power

264
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:40,208
that I believed to be
a magician's right.

265
00:15:43,541 --> 00:15:45,208
[MAN] That's
why I am doing this.

266
00:15:45,291 --> 00:15:48,708
Not to save her but to prove
that my power is absolute

267
00:15:48,791 --> 00:15:51,208
and nothing can
stand in my way.

268
00:15:51,958 --> 00:15:55,875
[MAN] Ah, ahhh!

269
00:15:59,250 --> 00:16:01,541
[MAN] I am here for
myself, not for that poor,

270
00:16:01,625 --> 00:16:04,125
pathetic woman.
It's not about her.

271
00:16:04,208 --> 00:16:05,916
It was never about her.

272
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,666
You're wrong.

273
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:10,875
You're lying to yourself.
Your bow's power.

274
00:16:10,958 --> 00:16:13,875
It's been amplified too much,
and the contents of your mind

275
00:16:13,958 --> 00:16:16,333
are beginning to
bleed out into mine.

276
00:16:16,416 --> 00:16:18,291
[INDEX] That's how I know.

277
00:16:18,375 --> 00:16:22,208
I know the truth. You're
simply in love with her.

278
00:16:22,291 --> 00:16:24,166
That's why you're risking
your life to prevent her

279
00:16:24,250 --> 00:16:25,833
from dying.

280
00:16:25,916 --> 00:16:28,250
You're willing to do
anything, to hurt anybody

281
00:16:28,333 --> 00:16:31,333
who gets in your way,
as long as you can save her.

282
00:16:31,416 --> 00:16:32,791
[INDEX] But you're
afraid if you admit that,

283
00:16:32,875 --> 00:16:35,500
then the blame for your
actions will fall on her.

284
00:16:35,583 --> 00:16:38,458
So you need to stop this now
before you go any further.

285
00:16:38,541 --> 00:16:40,333
I'm sure using a
grimoire is not the way

286
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:42,375
she would want you to help her!

287
00:16:47,541 --> 00:16:49,166
Toma!

288
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:50,541
[KAMIJO] Ah!

289
00:16:50,625 --> 00:16:57,916
♪

290
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,833
Toma. Toma!

291
00:16:59,916 --> 00:17:02,458
[KAMIJO] Geez, you sure
know how to make a guy worry!

292
00:17:02,541 --> 00:17:04,416
[INDEX] You know, I never
did get to eat my snack.

293
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:06,291
[KAMIJO] I'll feed you all
the food you can eat later.

294
00:17:06,375 --> 00:17:07,708
[INDEX] No, now!

295
00:17:07,791 --> 00:17:09,541
Is this truly wrong?

296
00:17:09,625 --> 00:17:13,458
What I've done. Choosing to
protect somebody else's life

297
00:17:13,541 --> 00:17:15,500
even if it means
losing my own.

298
00:17:15,583 --> 00:17:17,916
Is that really so wrong of me?

299
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:24,708
♪

300
00:17:24,791 --> 00:17:27,125
You fool. Of course it is.

301
00:17:33,375 --> 00:17:35,416
[KAMIJO] Do you
know how it feels...

302
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:38,500
to have somebody you
care about die on you?

303
00:17:39,416 --> 00:17:41,458
[KAMIJO] To see them in pain...

304
00:17:41,541 --> 00:17:43,583
To watch them suffer...

305
00:17:43,666 --> 00:17:45,666
And know there's
nothing you can do.

306
00:17:46,958 --> 00:17:49,458
You know that powerless
feeling, don't you?

307
00:17:49,541 --> 00:17:51,333
You feel it for her.

308
00:17:51,875 --> 00:17:53,291
[KAMIJO] To know that
she's dying makes you

309
00:17:53,375 --> 00:17:56,083
panic and grieve,
and it scares you so much

310
00:17:56,166 --> 00:17:58,125
that it shakes you
to your very core.

311
00:17:58,208 --> 00:17:59,708
It makes you want
to scream as the tears

312
00:17:59,791 --> 00:18:01,916
are running down your face.

313
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,666
And that's exactly
why it's wrong!

314
00:18:03,750 --> 00:18:05,291
You'd be passing
all of that to her.

315
00:18:05,375 --> 00:18:07,833
And you don't get to
choose that for somebody!

316
00:18:09,375 --> 00:18:10,875
[MAN coughs]

317
00:18:21,291 --> 00:18:23,041
[MAN] Pathetic.

318
00:18:23,125 --> 00:18:26,625
Look at me, after
reading just one volume.

319
00:18:26,708 --> 00:18:29,833
I'm broken. How could
I actually have expected

320
00:18:29,916 --> 00:18:31,916
this poor vessel to
contain the knowledge

321
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:35,125
and power of even a
single one of the grimoires?

322
00:18:35,208 --> 00:18:36,583
[MAN chuckles]

323
00:18:36,666 --> 00:18:40,041
My story is just a series
of futile fights for power.

324
00:18:40,125 --> 00:18:42,958
Three times now I've
given up on my life.

325
00:18:45,208 --> 00:18:47,916
But when I did,
there was still one thing

326
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:50,125
I couldn't give up on...

327
00:18:50,208 --> 00:18:54,500
One reason, one person
to keep fighting for.

328
00:18:54,583 --> 00:19:04,583
♪

329
00:19:08,416 --> 00:19:09,916
[Sphinx screeches]

330
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:10,791
Ahhh!

331
00:19:10,875 --> 00:19:13,333
[MAN] Ah-haha! Ah-ha!

332
00:19:13,416 --> 00:19:14,791
[KAMIJO] After everything
you've put us through,

333
00:19:14,875 --> 00:19:16,958
you don't get to
end it that easily.

334
00:19:17,041 --> 00:19:19,541
[KAMIJO] That was for
destroying my homework.

335
00:19:19,625 --> 00:19:21,708
Jerk. Do you have any idea

336
00:19:21,791 --> 00:19:23,333
how much trouble
I'm gonna be in?

337
00:19:23,416 --> 00:19:24,416
What?

338
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:25,666
[KAMIJO] Now then...

339
00:19:25,750 --> 00:19:27,791
Where's this woman you
want to save so badly?

340
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:29,958
[coughing]

341
00:19:30,041 --> 00:19:31,708
I don't.

342
00:19:31,791 --> 00:19:33,041
Where is she?

343
00:19:33,125 --> 00:19:35,041
We're gonna see if there's
a way we can help her.

344
00:19:35,125 --> 00:19:37,250
Without using a grimoire.

345
00:19:38,458 --> 00:19:40,333
You saw my right
hand, didn't you?

346
00:19:40,416 --> 00:19:42,333
I'm no magician, of course.

347
00:19:42,416 --> 00:19:44,833
And I don't know all
that much about curses.

348
00:19:44,916 --> 00:19:46,375
But if I'm right...

349
00:19:46,458 --> 00:19:49,125
one touch from my hand
should be enough to save her.

350
00:19:49,208 --> 00:19:50,791
[gasps]

351
00:19:50,875 --> 00:19:53,000
What? No.
That's crazy.

352
00:19:53,083 --> 00:19:54,958
I know it may
be hard to believe,

353
00:19:55,041 --> 00:19:57,291
but I have done this
sort of thing before.

354
00:20:00,708 --> 00:20:04,458
All right, then. Let's
go. You can lead the way.

355
00:20:04,541 --> 00:20:07,208
I promise, we're going
to help the woman you love.

356
00:20:07,291 --> 00:20:10,791
But we can't do it alone;
were gonna need you, too.

357
00:20:10,875 --> 00:20:12,833
[KAMIJO] So get up
and dust yourself off.

358
00:20:12,916 --> 00:20:14,541
You do want to help her, right?

359
00:20:14,625 --> 00:20:16,000
No matter what it takes?

360
00:20:16,083 --> 00:20:22,750
[crying]

361
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:23,916
Oh, honestly.

362
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,833
Now I have to deal
with a magical curse.

363
00:20:25,916 --> 00:20:28,958
How do I keep getting myself
in to these situations?

364
00:20:29,875 --> 00:20:31,791
Well, there's no
time like the present.

365
00:20:31,875 --> 00:20:35,125
Why don't we get going?
We've got a curse to kill.

366
00:20:35,208 --> 00:20:45,166
♪ [Ending Song] ♪

367
00:22:06,333 --> 00:22:08,625
[water sloshing]

368
00:22:08,708 --> 00:22:18,041
[metal clinking]

369
00:22:19,583 --> 00:22:29,583
♪

370
00:22:43,666 --> 00:22:46,791
[groaning]

371
00:22:46,875 --> 00:22:51,541
[KNIGHT 1A] Do you even know
who exactly it is that...

372
00:22:51,625 --> 00:22:55,583
ah... that you...
just attacked?

373
00:22:57,250 --> 00:23:00,625
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Sad, isn't it?
England's vaunted knighthood.

374
00:23:00,708 --> 00:23:02,625
Brought down so brutally.

375
00:23:03,833 --> 00:23:06,541
Did you come here
to try and stop me?

376
00:23:06,625 --> 00:23:07,791
[TSUCHIMIKADO]
Actually, I was never told

377
00:23:07,875 --> 00:23:09,458
to personally stop you.

378
00:23:09,541 --> 00:23:12,250
Besides, I have my
own task to see to.

379
00:23:12,333 --> 00:23:14,333
[KANZAKI] And where are
your orders coming from?

380
00:23:14,416 --> 00:23:16,958
The English Puritan
Church or Academy City?

381
00:23:17,041 --> 00:23:18,666
[TSUCHIMIKADO]
That's a good question.

382
00:23:18,750 --> 00:23:20,750
Though, if you think about it,

383
00:23:20,833 --> 00:23:22,708
I'm sure you
can figure it out.

384
00:23:22,791 --> 00:23:25,458
Well, I guess it would
be more accurate to say,

385
00:23:25,541 --> 00:23:28,125
if you think about
whose spy I am.

386
00:23:31,125 --> 00:23:33,125
[KANZAKI] In any case,
I'm leaving now.

387
00:23:33,208 --> 00:23:35,708
Feel free to report
to your superiors.

388
00:23:35,791 --> 00:23:37,458
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Oh, yeah? Eh...

389
00:23:37,541 --> 00:23:39,583
I'll just take
care of this bunch.

390
00:23:39,666 --> 00:23:41,291
[KANZAKI] I owe you one.

391
00:23:42,625 --> 00:23:45,375
So anyway, I have to admit,
I'm kind of curious.

392
00:23:45,458 --> 00:23:48,375
What would make you travel
all the way here from England?

393
00:23:50,291 --> 00:23:51,875
[KANZAKI] Good question.

394
00:23:56,583 --> 00:23:58,666
[KAMIJO] The arrival of
an old friend brings news of

395
00:23:58,750 --> 00:24:00,791
a missing grimoire
and a kidnapped nun.

396
00:24:00,875 --> 00:24:02,250
With so many factions fighting,

397
00:24:02,333 --> 00:24:04,041
things are bound
to get complicated.

398
00:24:04,958 --> 00:24:06,625
[KAMIJO] Next time,
"The Book of the Law."

399
00:24:06,708 --> 00:24:10,083
When science and magic
cross paths, a story is born.

